49
00:01:59.586 --> 00:02:02.990 line:-2 align:center
and the Bold Text
accessibility feature.


50
00:02:03.023 --> 00:02:06.326 line:-2 align:center
SF Symbols are also available
in three scales:


51
00:02:06.360 --> 00:02:09.162 line:-1 align:center
small, medium, and large.


52
00:02:10.163 --> 00:02:12.666 line:-2 align:center
These scales maintain
the same point size,


53
00:02:12,699 --> 00:02:14,334 line:-1
changing only their scales,


54
00:02:14,368 --> 00:02:17,504 line:-2
with stroke thicknesses
that are optically adjusted


55
00:02:17,538 --> 00:02:19,940 line:-2
and weight-matched
with the text.


56
00:02:20,941 --> 00:02:24,211 line:-2
You also need to be aware
of two different alignments.


57
00:02:24,244 --> 00:02:26,713 line:-1
First is the vertical alignment.


58
00:02:26.747 --> 00:02:29.349 line:-2 align:center
Symbols are automatically
vertically centered


59
00:02:29.383 --> 00:02:31.018 line:-1 align:center
to San Francisco's cap-height


60
00:02:31,051 --> 00:02:33,187 line:-2
in all the different scales
and weights.


61
00:02:34.188 --> 00:02:35.489 line:-1 align:center
And as you may know,


62
00:02:35,522 --> 00:02:38,025 line:-2
some symbols
have negative margins.


63
00:02:38,058 --> 00:02:41,595 line:-2
These margins are there to aid
with horizontal alignments.


64
00:02:41,628 --> 00:02:42,462 line:-1
That is the case


65
00:02:42,496 --> 00:02:45,532 line:-2
for most variants with badges,
for example.


66
00:02:45,566 --> 00:02:47,067 line:-1
When displayed in the UIs,


67
00:02:47.100 --> 00:02:49.269 line:-2 align:center
symbols will be
horizontally centered,


68
00:02:49,303 --> 00:02:51,205 line:-1
giving a consistent look,


69
00:02:51.238 --> 00:02:54.741 line:-2 align:center
especially when displaying
similar symbol variants.


70
00:02:55.742 --> 00:02:59.513 line:-2 align:center
If you want to learn more about
all the features in SF Symbols,


71
00:02:59.546 --> 00:03:02.716 line:-1 align:center
last year’s session from WWDC20


72
00:03:02,749 --> 00:03:04,751 line:-1
will get you up to speed.


73
00:03:05,485 --> 00:03:08,322 line:-2
Now let's talk
about symbol variants.


74
00:03:08,355 --> 00:03:09,823 line:-1
A symbol is defined


75
00:03:09,857 --> 00:03:12,392 line:-2
as a representation
of a symbolic value


76
00:03:12.426 --> 00:03:14.962 line:-2 align:center
that is used for the purpose
of communication.


77
00:03:14,995 --> 00:03:16,763 line:-1
For example, the word "love"


78
00:03:16,797 --> 00:03:18,732 line:-1
is represented by a heart.


79
00:03:18,765 --> 00:03:21,768 line:-2
In UIs, a symbol
is part of a visual system


80
00:03:21.802 --> 00:03:23.303 line:-1 align:center
that conveys meaning.


81
00:03:23,337 --> 00:03:25,539 line:-2
To enrich
this communication system,


82
00:03:25.572 --> 00:03:27.641 line:-2 align:center
a symbol
with the same representation


83
00:03:27,674 --> 00:03:29,576 line:-2
can come
in many different forms.


84
00:03:30.577 --> 00:03:32.479 line:-1 align:center
In SF Symbols, the default,


85
00:03:32,513 --> 00:03:33,714 line:-1
or universal variant,


86
00:03:33,747 --> 00:03:36,049 line:-2
is the outlined version
of a symbol


87
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:38,151 line:-1
as it relates to the typography


88
00:03:38,185 --> 00:03:39,620 line:-1
in the way that we can imagine


89
00:03:39,653 --> 00:03:43,123 line:-2
the same tool
drawing the symbol and the text.


90
00:03:43,156 --> 00:03:44,958 line:-1
In the absence of context,


91
00:03:44,992 --> 00:03:46,894 line:-1
outlined is the default.


92
00:03:47,895 --> 00:03:50,664 line:-2
And when we want to make
a symbol more prominent,


93
00:03:50.697 --> 00:03:52.799 line:-2 align:center
like when we want it
to have more surface area


94
00:03:52.833 --> 00:03:55.736 line:-2 align:center
to saturate with color
for the purpose of selection,


95
00:03:55,769 --> 00:03:58,005 line:-2
the filled variant
is a great choice.


96
00:03:59.773 --> 00:04:01.074 line:-1 align:center
In SF Symbols,


97
00:04:01.108 --> 00:04:03.677 line:-2 align:center
a symbol may come
in many different forms.


98
00:04:03.710 --> 00:04:06.947 line:-2 align:center
We have outlined
and filled variants.


99
00:04:06,980 --> 00:04:08,649 line:-1
We also have slash variants,


100
00:04:08,682 --> 00:04:10,284 line:-1
which are used to convey


101
00:04:10,317 --> 00:04:11,852 line:-1
the functions of removing


102
00:04:11,885 --> 00:04:15,088 line:-2
or displaying an item
as inactive or unavailable.


103
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:17,658 line:-1
We have enclosing variants


104
00:04:17,691 --> 00:04:19,593 line:-2
that are contained
inside a shape


105
00:04:19,626 --> 00:04:22,930 line:-2
like a circle,
square, or rectangle.


106
00:04:24.231 --> 00:04:27.267 line:-2 align:center
All these variants
help make the UIs richer


107
00:04:27,301 --> 00:04:28,802 line:-1
and give more flexibility


108
00:04:28,836 --> 00:04:30,938 line:-2
when setting up
visual hierarchies


109
00:04:30,971 --> 00:04:34,107 line:-2
with the interface elements
and the content.


110
00:04:34,141 --> 00:04:35,609 line:-1
A clear visual system


111
00:04:35.642 --> 00:04:37.678 line:-2 align:center
will go to great lengths
in reducing


112
00:04:37,711 --> 00:04:39,246 line:-1
the appearance of complexity,


113
00:04:39.279 --> 00:04:42.082 line:-2 align:center
even when the actions themselves
are complex.


114
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:43,050 line:-1
Consequently,


115
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:45,953 line:-2
knowing where to use
a symbol variant is essential.


116
00:04:45,986 --> 00:04:48,055 line:-1
A filled symbol in swipe actions


117
00:04:48.088 --> 00:04:49.389 line:-1 align:center
and iOS tab bars


118
00:04:49,423 --> 00:04:52,526 line:-2
give a consistent appearance
and level of emphasis,


119
00:04:52,559 --> 00:04:55,863 line:-2
giving better control in areas
that indicate selection


120
00:04:55.896 --> 00:04:58.565 line:-2 align:center
when defined
with an accent color.


121
00:04:59,233 --> 00:05:01,835 line:-2
A symbol inside a circle
with a filled variant


122
00:05:01,869 --> 00:05:05,439 line:-2
provides better legibility
at small sizes.


123
00:05:06.273 --> 00:05:08.909 line:-2 align:center
And an outlined,
or default variant, of a symbol


124
00:05:08,942 --> 00:05:12,446 line:-2
is great for Toolbars,
Navigation Bars, Lists


125
00:05:12,479 --> 00:05:14,348 line:-1
and other places in the UI


126
00:05:14,381 --> 00:05:17,484 line:-2
where symbols
are presented alongside text


127
00:05:17.518 --> 00:05:19.186 line:-1 align:center
or where symbols need to display


128
00:05:19,219 --> 00:05:21,388 line:-1
a uniform appearance.


129
00:05:21,421 --> 00:05:25,092 line:-2
When designing your own symbols,
remember to be consistent


130
00:05:25,125 --> 00:05:27,995 line:-2
and define a system
that meets the user's needs.


131
00:05:28.028 --> 00:05:28.862 line:-1 align:center
In this way,


132
00:05:28.896 --> 00:05:30.764 line:-2 align:center
you will help perceive
visual metaphors


133
00:05:30,797 --> 00:05:32,799 line:-2
that are directly related
to the actions


134
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:34,434 line:-1
that the symbols initiate


135
00:05:34,468 --> 00:05:36,970 line:-2
or the content
the symbols represent.


136
00:05:37.004 --> 00:05:40.174 line:-2 align:center
As symbols become available
on all platforms,


137
00:05:40,207 --> 00:05:42,476 line:-2
the SF Symbols library
keeps growing,


138
00:05:42,509 --> 00:05:45,913 line:-2
with nearly 600 new symbols
available this year.


139
00:05:45.946 --> 00:05:49.683 line:-2 align:center
We have expanded
the Apple products and devices.


140
00:05:50,684 --> 00:05:54,655 line:-2
And we have new additions
for video game controllers.


141
00:05:55.656 --> 00:05:58.625 line:-2 align:center
We have
some health-related symbols,


142
00:05:58,659 --> 00:06:01,929 line:-2
with plenty of new symbols
to represent communication.


143
00:06:02.930 --> 00:06:04.464 line:-1 align:center
And new inset symbols


144
00:06:04,498 --> 00:06:06,133 line:-1
that are helpful for designs


145
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:07,968 line:-1
related to interface layout


146
00:06:08.001 --> 00:06:10.037 line:-1 align:center
and window management.


147
00:06:11.038 --> 00:06:13.974 line:-2 align:center
We also designed
some symbols for watchOS.


148
00:06:14.975 --> 00:06:18.145 line:-2 align:center
And we have many
new objects to choose from,


149
00:06:19,146 --> 00:06:21,215 line:-1
making SF Symbols a library


150
00:06:21.248 --> 00:06:24.551 line:-2 align:center
with more than 3,000 symbols
to choose from.


151
00:06:25,619 --> 00:06:28,255 line:-2
Now let's talk
about localization.


152
00:06:28.288 --> 00:06:30.757 line:-2 align:center
At Apple,
we seek to make interfaces


153
00:06:30.791 --> 00:06:32.392 line:-1 align:center
more inclusive and tailored


154
00:06:32.426 --> 00:06:35.629 line:-2 align:center
for international
and multicultural audiences.


155
00:06:36,630 --> 00:06:38,232 line:-1
This year, we have expanded


156
00:06:38.265 --> 00:06:40.634 line:-1 align:center
the SF Symbols script coverage


157
00:06:40.667 --> 00:06:43.437 line:-1 align:center
with new symbols for Arabic,


158
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:44,938 line:-1
Hebrew,


159
00:06:44,972 --> 00:06:46,974 line:-1
and Devanagari,


160
00:06:47,007 --> 00:06:49,776 line:-1
and included designs for Thai,


161
00:06:49.810 --> 00:06:51.512 line:-1 align:center
Chinese,


162
00:06:51.545 --> 00:06:53.013 line:-1 align:center
Japanese,


163
00:06:53.046 --> 00:06:54.047 line:-1 align:center
and Korean.


164
00:06:57,084 --> 00:06:58,185 line:-1
We made it easy


165
00:06:58,218 --> 00:07:00,487 line:-2
